init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not really in the mood of issuing any orders."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee buzzed slightly and hovered around me.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "What would you like to have me do?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You must issue an order," said the bee.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: , I could tell them to do whatever I wanted.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "They say they will do so." said the bee.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "By the way, why did you call me your majesty?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee buzzed and flew over to the flower on the other side of the room.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But at least I didn't have to worry about the bees stinging me.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: My allergy was gone and I could live a normal life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I just wished the bee would have told me why he thought I was his queen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He buzzed and said "My queen, you are the most beautiful woman I have ever seen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: My bee and I made a promise to be friends forever.
